    "brand_story_combo_JeTTXn": {
      "type": "brand-story-combo",
      "name": "Story Layout Bundle",
      "settings": {
        "layout": "image-left",
        "width": "wrapper",
        "top_heading": "<p><strong>What drew you to seek inspiration in Verona?</strong></p>",
        "top_text": "<p>Well, I like Verona and its 2000 years of incredible history. And I go to the Verona vineyards often to meet my close friends. [Ed. Note: It’s just an hour’s drive from Roberto’s atelier in Vicenza.]</p><p>But every collection begins with a story. And it is the love story that drew me to Verona. It is a sad story, Romeo and Juliet.</p><p>Let’s be quite honest about it, it is a tragedy. But it is a tragedy of intense emotions, which are missing today, worldwide. Real emotions. A story of two people who went against the world, their families, because they were in love. And in the end, they were together only when they died. So, it is an unforgettable tragedy about strong sentiments. For them, love is everything.<strong><br/><br/>\"Flowers represent romanticism, they are a symbol of love.\"</strong></p>",
        "top_image": "shopify://shop_images/Roberto_Coin_Image8.png",
        "caption_text": "",
        "padding_top": 120,
        "padding_bottom": 0,
        "padding_top_mobile": 60,
        "padding_bottom_mobile": 0
      }
    },
    "brand_story_combo_XLKqVK": {
      "type": "brand-story-combo",
      "name": "Story Layout Bundle",
      "settings": {
        "layout": "image-right",
        "width": "wrapper",
        "top_heading": "<p><strong>A flower design is at the heart of the Love in Verona collection. What inspired the collection's floral motif?</strong></p>",
        "top_text": "<p><em>In the medieval period, the time of Romeo and Juliet, can you imagine the hills of Verona? It was all natural flowers. And in the Renaissance, the time of Shakespeare, flowers are everywhere and they represent romanticism, they are a symbol of love. I decided to take all this and put it in a bracelet, decorated with the renaissance flowers, and representing the perfect love.</em></p>",
        "top_image": "shopify://shop_images/Roberto_Coin_Image9.png",
        "caption_text": "",
        "padding_top": 120,
        "padding_bottom": 0,
        "padding_top_mobile": 60,
        "padding_bottom_mobile": 0
      }
    },
